            <div class="span9">
                <div class="page-header"><h1> Installing LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices<small></small></h1></div>
                 <p>
        To install the LearnPad software on an OEM device please follow the instructions below step by step:
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <p>
                Open the Settings application and ensure you have a tick in the <span class="menuReference">Unknown Sources</span> option
				(to allow installations of applications from other sources).
                Accept the warning when prompted.
            </p>
            <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/accessibility-page.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/accessibility-page.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/accessibility-page.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="nstalling LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
            <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/accessibility-page.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/accessibility-page.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/accessibility-page.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="Installing LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
             <div style="clear: both"></div>
             <br/>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Open a web browser and ensure you are connected to the internet.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Navigate to
                <a href="http://learnpad.co/install">
                    http://learnpad.co/install
                </a>
                This will automatically download the installation .apk file and notify you in the status bar as shown below.
				Once downloaded, press it to initiate the installation of the LearnPad config application and press <span class="buttonReference">Install</span> to confirm.
            </p>
                        <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/browser-window.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/browser-window.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/browser-window.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="nstalling LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
            <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/installing-config.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/installing-config.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/installing-config.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="Installing LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
             <div style="clear: both"></div>
             <br/>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Once installed, press on Open to open the application. You will see the config screen shown below.
            </p>
                        <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/config-installed.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/config-installed.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/config-installed.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="nstalling LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
            <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/config-settings.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/config-settings.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/config-settings.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="Installing LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
             <div style="clear: both"></div>
             <br/>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Press the <span class="propertyReference">Check Now</span> link. This will initiate a download and installation of additional applications. 
				You will see a number of installation dialogs pop up, press to install each of these in turn and when prompted, press the done button after installation
            </p>
           <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/install-confirm.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/install-confirm.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/install-confirm.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="nstalling LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
            <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/install-done.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/install-done.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/install-done.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="Installing LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
             <div style="clear: both"></div>
             <br/>
           
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                After the installations have completed, press the Home key. You will see a <span class="menuReference">Complete Action Using</span> dialogue box.
				Press to put a tick in the <span class="propertyReference">Use by default for this action</span> 
				then select <span class="menuReference">LearnPad</span>. 
				You will then see the LearnPad interface (NOTE: This may be blank until a profile has been loaded).
            </p>
                       <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/launcher-selection.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/launcher-selection.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/launcher-selection.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="nstalling LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
            <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/learnpad-unlocked.jpg" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/learnpad-unlocked.jpg" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/learnpad-unlocked.jpg" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="Installing LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
             <div style="clear: both"></div>
             <br/>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                To now lock the LearnPad so that only the approved applications and websites can be accessed press the 
				<span class="buttonReference">Lock LearnPad</span> button. 
				The first time this is done you will be asked to enable the <span class="menuReference">Accessibility Service</span> as shown below.
            </p>
                       <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/accessibility-prompt.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/accessibility-prompt.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/accessibility-prompt.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="nstalling LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
            <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/accessibility-page.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/accessibility-page.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/accessibility-page.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="Installing LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
             <div style="clear: both"></div>
             <br/>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Press to put a tick in both the <span class="propertyReference">Accessibility</span> 
				and <span class="propertyReference">LearnPad</span> entries. 
				When complete, press the home key to return to the LearnPad launcher. 
				Press the <span class="buttonReference">Lock LearnPad</span> button once more to lock the device.
				If you are prompted again by the <span class="menuReference">Complete Action Using</span> dialogue, 
				put a tick in the <span class="propertyReference">Use by default for this action</span> then select <span class="menuReference">LearnPad</span> 
				then press the <span class="buttonReference">Lock LearnPad</span> button again. 
				Once locked, LearnPad will remain locked down even after a power off/on cycle.
            </p>
            <div class="view view-first span2">
                                <a href="../assets/images/support/learnpad-menu.png" rel="prettyPhoto">  <img src="../assets/images/support/learnpad-menu.png" alt="" /></a>
                                <div class="mask">
                                    <a href="../assets/images/support/learnpad-menu.png" rel="prettyPhoto" class="info"><img src="../assets/img/plus.png" alt="Installing LearnPad on 3<sup>rd</sup> Party Devices" /></a>
                                </div>
                             </div>
             <div style="clear: both"></div>
             <br/>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                You will now need to <a href="enroll-learnpad.aspx">enroll your device</a> and <a href="changing-profiles.aspx">select a profile</a>.
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
    <h3>
        Troubleshooting
    </h3>
    <ul>
        <li id="failedToDownload">
            <p class="question">
                When trying to download LearnPad I get the message "Failed to download"
            </p>
            <p class="answer">
                Make sure you have access to the LearnPad data server
                by going to <a href="http://data.learnpad.co/index.htm" target="_blank">http://data.learnpad.co/index.htm</a>.
                If you cannot see this website from your LearnPad, contact your local IT administrator.
            </p>
            <p class="answer">
                Make sure your network allows Android application (APK) files
                by <a href="http://learnpad.co/install">downloading the file</a> to your desktop or laptop computer.
                If it won't download, contact your local IT administrator.
            </p>
        </li>
    </ul>
